#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn21.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga "
msgstr "1. Monks "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Nandasutta "
msgstr "8. With Nanda "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.281, sc1
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: This is perhaps the clearest mention of northern black polished ware in the suttas. https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/nanda-and-northern-black-polished-ware/2919
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā nando bhagavato mātucchāputto ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni pārupitvā akkhīni añjetvā acchaṃ pattaṃ gahetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ nandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Nanda—the Buddha’s cousin on his mother’s side—dressed in nicely pressed and ironed robes, applied eyeshadow, and took a polished black bowl. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.3"
msgid "“na kho te taṃ, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni pārupeyyāsi, akkhīni ca añjeyyāsi, acchañca pattaṃ dhāreyyāsi. "
msgstr "“Nanda, as a gentleman who has gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness, it’s not appropriate for you to dress in nicely pressed and ironed robes, apply eyeshadow, and carry a polished black bowl. "

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.4"
msgid "Etaṃ kho te, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ āraññiko ca assasi, piṇḍapātiko ca paṃsukūliko ca kāmesu ca anapekkho vihareyyāsī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s appropriate for you to stay in the wilderness, eat only alms-food, wear rag robes, and live without concern for sensual pleasures.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.6"
msgid "satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.1"
msgid "“Kadāhaṃ nandaṃ passeyyaṃ, "
msgstr "“When will I see Nanda "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.2"
msgid "āraññaṃ paṃsukūlikaṃ; "
msgstr "in the wilderness, wearing rag robes, "

# NOTE: uncha = ounce!
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.3"
msgid "Aññātuñchena yāpentaṃ, "
msgstr "feeding on scraps offered by strangers, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.4"
msgid "kāmesu anapekkhinan”ti. "
msgstr "unconcerned for sensual pleasures?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn21.8:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā nando aparena samayena āraññiko ca piṇḍapātiko ca paṃsukūliko ca kāmesu ca anapekkho vihāsīti. "
msgstr "Then some time later Venerable Nanda stayed in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and lived without concern for sensual pleasures. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.8:3.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

